org.pircbotx.hooks

Class TemporaryListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pircbotx.hooks.ListenerAdapter
      • org.pircbotx.hooks.TemporaryListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Listener

    public class TemporaryListener
extends ListenerAdapter
    Listener that provides an easy way to make temporary listeners that aren't needed after one use

    Your listener will only get called if the bot that generated the event matches the given one. Then when you are finished, call done() and the listener will be removed.

    Note: The reason the done() method is used instead of automatically removing is that you may need to check for something before executing.

    Author:
    Leon Blakey
